comment:
At first, it's easy to dismiss the Judge/AH connections as conspiracy theory. Until you learn things like: Nicol's son works with defendant Dan Wootton at Talk Radio, which, like the Sun, is also owned by Murdock. In short, Nicol's son works both with & for the defendants in the case... That's pretty significant. 

But then you add a multitude of curiosities and/or "coincidences"...

Like say AH giving speeches at Nicol's firm - after- he was assigned as judge to the case. 

Or say, Kathy Lette throwing AH a party... Who cares about a party right? How about if I told you that the hostess, Kathe Lette, is a close friend of Judge Nicol's wife?  Would it seem a bit more relevant then? 

Or how about that Amber's lawyer Jen Robinson was mentored by man named Geoffrey Robertson. Who also just happens to have co-written a book with Judge Nicol and be Kathe Lette's ex-husband... 

On their own, these might be meaningless. I mean, the upper echelons of UK law are bound to be interconnected. And in fact, previous professional connections on their own are not grounds for an appeal  on the basis of judiciary bias. 

But there seems to be too many connections here; both previous & current, and both professional & personal. Again, alone, likely insignificant. Together, they suggest that impartiality would be very difficult here and that Nicol should have recused himself.  https://photos.app.goo.gl/inMFURtAcUuEnNHR9

There are various Twitter posts and YouTube videos elaborating on the details of those links.
